Usage: compress_special [-help] [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}] [-incremental]
                        [-layers <layer>+] [-nets <net>+]

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}     # Specifies the coordinates for the area from which to
                        # compress PG.
                        # Only special wires and special vias within the
                        # specified area will be compressed.
                        # Default: Compress all PG structure. (box, optional)
-incremental            # This option can only be specified when the current
                        # design is in compressed mode. Call -incremental to
                        # re-compress the PG.
                        # You can use it after you edit PG wires or vias.
                        # (bool, optional)
-layers <layer>+        # Specifies the layers on which to compress PG. You
                        # must use LEF layer names or a routing layer index
                        # value (1 for the first routing layer, 2 for the
                        # second routing layer, and so on). ((layer)+, optional)
-nets <net>+            # Specifies the nets from which to compress PG.
                        # If the specified net doesn't have any special routes
                        # on it, the net will be ignored. ((net)+, optional)